# Real Data Integration Complete

Synthetic fallback data has been completely stripped from the application, ensuring that the DropGravity Pro Engine only serves **real market signals** moving forward.

## What was Changed

### 1. Synthetic Data Eradication
- Removed `fallbackProducts` and all legacy fake data arrays from [server/index.js](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/server/index.js).
- Removed imports and usages of `generateProducts` and `getSignalStrength` inside the core API endpoints.
- If real data cannot be scraped, or if the API connection drops, the application will now strictly return a `502 Bad Gateway` error rather than blindly generating mock products. 

### 2. Hardened Amazon Scraper ([amazonService.js](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/server/services/amazonService.js))
- Replaced the simple scraper configuration with **advanced User-Agent rotation, hardened headers (`Sec-Fetch`, `Accept`, etc.), and strict Cache-Control**.
- Added **explicit CAPTCHA detection**: The scraper now instantly detects if Amazon has served a CAPTCHA block and halts to prevent data pollution.
- Integrated an internal **Retry Loop**: If a transient network block or scrape failure occurs, the server will wait 1.5 seconds and retry automatically to maximize the chances of retrieving real results.

### 3. Strict Google Trends API ([trendService.js](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/server/services/trendService.js))
- Refactored [computeScore](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/server/services/trendService.js#3-46) to strictly `throw` an error if it encounters empty timelines, eliminating the previous behavior where missing data defaulted to a fake score of `50`.
- Implemented a resilient **Retry Loop** directly in the [fetchTrendData](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/server/services/trendService.js#47-94) pipeline.

### 4. Dynamic & Cached Trending API (`/api/products/trending`)
- Transformed the static trending endpoint into a fully live engine. It now selects curated keywords based on the date, actively scrapes Amazon, grades the products through the engine, and queries Google Trends.
- **Implemented 6-Hour Caching**: Both `AmazonCache` and `TrendCache` are now strictly enforced on the trending page. This drastically improves load times on the Finder UI and prevents Amazon from IP-banning the server due to excessive repeated queries.

## Validation Results
- Verified that `grep generateProducts` no longer returns any hits outside of [productGenerator.js](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/server/engine/productGenerator.js) (which is now effectively retired from the main pipeline).
- Both `npm run dev` and `node server/index.js` start and run without syntax or reference errors.
- The system is now 100% reliant on real scraping signals.
